ong>two types of disruptive innovation</strong>, one in which a new entrant=
 brings new customers into the market, and another in which a new entrant c=
aptures the low end of the market at a lower cost.&nbsp;<strong>These firms=
 did both</strong>.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">By integrating delivery capabilities into t=
he food delivery value chain, restaurants that did not have delivery capabi=
lities were now able to deliver via UberEats or Doordash, at times <a href=
